properties.headline: COVID-19 Queensland Border Control
properties.otherAdvice:
Persons may enter Queensland subject to obtaining a Queensland Border Declaration Pass and undertaking to present for a COVID-19 test if they develop symptoms.

There are restrictions on entry for people who are from, or have recently been to a COVID-19 Hotspot; check the website before travelling or attempting to obtain a Border Declaration Pass: https://www.qld.gov.au/health/conditions/health-alerts/coronavirus-covid-19/current-status/hotspots-covid-19

Traffic volumes and operational requirements at checkpoints will cause delays. Please allow plenty of additional travel time to cross the NSW-Queensland border, particularly during peak periods.

Heavy vehicles entering Queensland must hold and display a Queensland border pass. For more information: https://www.qld.gov.au/border-pass-confirmation.

properties.headline: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS Parramatta Light Rail - PARRAMATTA Macquarie Street between Harris Street, Harris Park AND Marsden Street
properties.adviceB: Use an alternative route; Allow extra travel time
properties.otherAdvice:
There will be changed traffic conditions in place from 8pm on May 1:

  • Macquarie St will be reduced to one westbound lane between Harris and Marsden streets to facilitate construction and utility works.
  • There will be no right turn from Charles St southbound into Macquarie St westbound.
  • There will be no right turn from Macquarie St into Horwood Pl. Entry to Horwood Pl will only be available from George St. The right turn movement from Horwood Pl onto Macquarie St westbound will be maintained.
  • Motorists are encouraged to use George St to travel west across Parramatta.

Changed Traffic Conditions from Friday 17 July to Monday 20 July (unless indicated otherwise):

  • Macquarie Street will be closed to traffic between Harris and Charles Street between 8pm Friday 17 July and 5am Saturday 18 July.         
  • Macquarie Street will also be closed to traffic between Charles and Smith Streets between 8pm Friday 17 July and 5am Monday 20 July.
  • One general traffic lane will be maintained on Charles Street through the intersection of Macquarie Street, for motorists travelling north and south, under the control of traffic management personnel.
  • There will be no access from Smith Street into Macquarie Street during this time.
  • Please note that the intersection of Charles and Macquarie Streets and all lanes on Smith Street will be available between 2:30pm and 8:30pm Saturday 18 July due to a special event at Bankwest Stadium.         
  • Motorists are encouraged to use George or Phillip Streets to travel west across Parramatta.
properties.displayName: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS Parramatta Light Rail

properties.publicTransport:

  • The bus stop north of the old Mororo Bridge that was temporarily relocated to Woombah Woods Caravan Park will be reinstated to its original location.  
  • The school bus stop at Banana Road has been relocated to Woombah Woods Caravan Park bus stop on Iluka Road.   
  • The 386 service and school bus route will again access Chatsworth Road north via the old Mororo Bridge.
properties.otherAdvice:

properties.headline: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS Oversize vehicles - MOUNT VICTORIA Great Western Highway to River Lett Hill
properties.otherAdvice:
A series of 70m-long loads will travel down Victoria Pass and up River Lett Hill early on Monday to Saturday mornings through to September. For the safety of motorists, changed traffic conditions will be in place.

Eastbound traffic will be held at River Lett Hill and the bottom of Mount Victoria while the trucks use these sections of road. Traffic will be stopped for 20-25 minutes between 4am and 5am.

Westbound motorists will experience delays while following the oversize vehicles because they will need to travel at low speed through this section.

properties.otherAdvice:
From 11am Sat 4 Jul until the operational launch of the Parramatta Light Rail:

Church Street will be closed to traffic in both directions between Victoria Road and Factory Street.

One southbound lane will be maintained on Church Street between Factory Street and Victoria Road for local access only.

There will be no through access at the following intersections along Church Street:

  • No access to Church Street from the eastern side of Albert Street.
  • No access to Church Street from the western side of Factory, Harold, Fennell and Ross Streets.
properties.diversions:
Motorists are encouraged to use OConnell Street to travel across
Parramatta during this time.

Southbound motorists:
Alternative petrol stations - Shell Service Station at Wilton Rd, Wilton, located 5km north and the Shell Service Station, Old Hume Hwy, Balaclava, located 23km south.
Alternative rest area - south of the Bargo off ramp at Yanderra.

Northbound motorists:
Alternative petrol stations - BP Service Station at Remembrance Driveway, Bargo, located 7km south and Douglas Park Service Station at Camden Rd, Douglas Park, located 13km north.
Alternative rest area - Berrima rest area.

properties.headline: COVID-19 Border Crossings - TOCUMWAL Newell Highway
properties.otherAdvice:
The NSW state government has imposed restrictions on movements to/from Victoria as a result of the coronavirus pandemic.

Motorists approaching this checkpoint must present a valid Border Crossing Permit to enter NSW.

Transport for NSW is continuing to work closely with NSW Health, NSW Police and industry on a number of important issues including freight operations and logistics.

Visit health.nsw.gov.au for more details.

OSOM operators should call 131 700 prior to arriving at border checkpoints so access can be arranged.

  • Most checkpoints have width restrictions which require movement of barriers before proceeding.
  • Calling ahead to seek instructions will reduce delays for all motorists. 
  • OSOM operators are asked to be patient and follow direction of NSW Police and Transport for NSW officers.

properties.otherAdvice:
The NSW state government has imposed restrictions on cross-border movements as a result of the coronavirus pandemic. All non-essential travel should be avoided. Restrictions in place include border road closures and police checks on vehicles on major highways.  

Essential workers can continue their work. The freight network will be maintained and supply chains managed. If you are travelling from Victoria to NSW, you will need a COVID-19 NSW border declaration permit.  

Police and other resources will be at the following locations to help you cross the border from Victoria into NSW as quickly as possible.  

  • Wodonga Pl, South Albury
  • Hume Hwy, South Albury
  • Cobb Hwy, Moama
  • Newell Hwy, Tocumwal
  • Sturt Hwy, Buronga
  • Princes Hwy, Timbillica
